James Robarge, 45, from Saxtons River, Vermont, was sentenced to 30 years to life in prison for second-degree murder in the death of his wife, Kelly Robarge .
Robarge's body was found 10 days later in Unity, New Hampshire, with her hands and head detached .
Kelly had filed for divorce after 24 years of marriage on June 27, 2013 .
Her brother, Ron Prouty Jr., told Robarge on Friday that he hoped he 'rotted in hell' during the sentencing .